00:28:46,740 --> 00:28:51,920
♪ Can you promise me that you will never forget me? ♪

281
00:28:57,780 --> 00:28:58,620
Whoa.

282
00:28:59,940 --> 00:29:02,820
About your dad's car, what a coincidence.

283
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:07,590
Your dad and mom must have wanted it to happen.

284
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:09,880
What do you mean?

285
00:29:12,300 --> 00:29:15,420
Oh, I mean your dad and mom must be happy.

286
00:29:18,080 --> 00:29:18,730
You're right.

287
00:29:19,620 --> 00:29:21,920
I didn't expect to find my dad's car here.

288
00:29:26,520 --> 00:29:27,800
Oh, Namping,

289
00:29:31,500 --> 00:29:32,630
what do you like to eat?

290
00:29:34,790 --> 00:29:35,880
I like strawberries.

291
00:29:36,630 --> 00:29:38,820
I like everything that has strawberries.

292
00:29:39,930 --> 00:29:40,800
What about you?

293
00:29:53,320 --> 00:29:54,790
Other than fixing cars,

294
00:29:55,880 --> 00:29:56,830
can you also fix electrical issues?

295
00:29:59,030 --> 00:29:59,380
What?

296
00:30:27,050 --> 00:30:27,800
Namping!

297
00:30:29,170 --> 00:30:29,810
Namping!

298
00:30:39,180 --> 00:30:40,220
The doorbell is broken.

299
00:30:41,860 --> 00:30:43,910
You can call me next time. You already have my number.

300
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:07,500
Hey.

301
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:09,270
Ping.

302
00:31:10,760 --> 00:31:11,120
Don't.

303
00:31:11,770 --> 00:31:12,430
I'll do it for you.

304
00:31:24,610 --> 00:31:25,280
Can you change it?

305
00:31:26,040 --> 00:31:26,600
Yes.

306
00:31:27,500 --> 00:31:28,030
It's the same size.

307
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:42,980
Ping!

308
00:31:44,310 --> 00:31:45,050
Are you okay?

309
00:31:53,510 --> 00:31:54,850
Why are you so shocked?

310
00:31:55,190 --> 00:31:56,130
I only broke a glass.

311
00:31:58,910 --> 00:31:59,210
Well,

312
00:31:59,880 --> 00:32:01,100
you're so clumsy!

313
00:32:01,470 --> 00:32:02,710
You’d better clean this up yourself.

314
00:32:03,790 --> 00:32:04,320
Okay.

315
00:32:05,100 --> 00:32:06,350
I know. There's no need to nag.

316
00:32:09,510 --> 00:32:09,910
Oh,

317
00:32:10,670 --> 00:32:12,480
I'll buy some food for you.

318
00:32:13,020 --> 00:32:15,460
Stir-fried crispy pork with basil and a fried egg, like usual, okay?

319
00:32:17,350 --> 00:32:17,720
Okay.

320
00:32:19,050 --> 00:32:19,840
X, do you want as well?

321
00:32:20,470 --> 00:32:21,830
It's okay.

322
00:32:22,460 --> 00:32:23,780
Never mind, I'll buy it for you too.

323
00:32:24,920 --> 00:32:26,220
Don't forget to clean this.

324
00:32:26,460 --> 00:32:27,340
Be more careful!

325
00:32:41,530 --> 00:32:42,340
Be careful!

326
00:33:37,110 --> 00:33:37,660
Thank you.

327
00:33:41,880 --> 00:33:42,300
It's okay.

328
00:33:43,620 --> 00:33:46,460
It would be more worse if you got cut on glass.

329
00:33:52,710 --> 00:33:53,820
I'll clean it up for you.

330
00:34:10,030 --> 00:34:10,440
Hey.

331
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:15,090
I think I will stay here longer.

332
00:34:17,280 --> 00:34:17,840
Really?

333
00:34:22,410 --> 00:34:23,110
Well...

334
00:34:25,110 --> 00:34:26,700
If you're free, you can come to the garage.

335
00:34:31,250 --> 00:34:32,420
You can check out the car you bought.

336
00:35:12,060 --> 00:35:12,650
Ahem!

337
00:35:14,470 --> 00:35:15,650
Is there anything you want to tell me?

338
00:35:17,910 --> 00:35:18,640
No.

339
00:35:19,960 --> 00:35:20,490
Are you sure?

340
00:35:21,950 --> 00:35:22,540
I'm sure.

341
00:35:26,230 --> 00:35:27,110
Let's get inside.

342
00:35:28,920 --> 00:35:29,310
Let's go.

343
00:35:29,840 --> 00:35:30,520
Are you sure?

344
00:35:33,090 --> 00:35:33,770
Okay, fine. Let's go.

345
00:35:34,480 --> 00:35:35,660
Let's eat.

346
00:35:37,180 --> 00:35:38,350
- Quickly!
- I know!

347
00:36:06,180 --> 00:36:07,310
Oh, hey!

348
00:36:07,980 --> 00:36:09,120
We met again.

349
00:36:09,670 --> 00:36:11,360
Is this your garage?

350
00:36:11,990 --> 00:36:13,300
No, I work here.

351
00:36:15,050 --> 00:36:15,820
What a coincidence.

352
00:36:16,930 --> 00:36:17,550
Well...

353
00:36:18,170 --> 00:36:20,370
Let's say that I've finally come to use your services here.

354
00:36:21,740 --> 00:36:22,890
And I'll pay this time.

355
00:36:24,140 --> 00:36:25,140
Cash only, correct?

356
00:36:25,990 --> 00:36:26,780
Good job!

357
00:36:27,580 --> 00:36:28,630
So what's wrong with your car?

358
00:36:30,220 --> 00:36:31,140
I don't know too.

359
00:36:31,410 --> 00:36:33,590
The car shakes while I’m driving.

360
00:36:34,880 --> 00:36:36,190
Alright, I'll take a look at it.

361
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:39,280
Excuse me.

362
00:36:58,580 --> 00:36:59,350
Whoa!

363
00:37:00,670 --> 00:37:01,900
There's a nail in your back tire.

364
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:02,370
What?

365
00:37:02,750 --> 00:37:03,840
You might accidentally run over it.

366
00:37:05,370 --> 00:37:06,950
Whoa! People these days.

367
00:37:07,530 --> 00:37:08,880
Why did they just throw it away carelessly?

368
00:37:10,990 --> 00:37:12,290
Why didn't they throw it in the bin?

369
00:37:14,130 --> 00:37:16,030
It's lucky that I didn't get into an accident.

370
00:37:17,150 --> 00:37:18,720
It's alright. I'll repair it for you.

371
00:38:19,690 --> 00:38:20,070
Mister!

372
00:38:22,430 --> 00:38:22,860
Mister.

373
00:38:24,530 --> 00:38:24,940
Mister!

374
00:38:28,680 --> 00:38:29,410
Your car is fixed.

375
00:38:32,340 --> 00:38:35,170
Sorry for making you wait. There are so many customers today.

376
00:38:38,790 --> 00:38:39,840
Your service is good.

377
00:38:42,260 --> 00:38:43,740
No wonder why there're so many customers.

378
00:38:45,040 --> 00:38:45,680
Thank you.

379
00:38:46,030 --> 00:38:48,970
I will come back to use your services again.

380
00:38:56,160 --> 00:38:57,440
He's the problem.

381
00:38:58,410 --> 00:38:59,270
That's my brother.

382
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:01,180
He's fixing a car for someone special to him.

383
00:39:01,900 --> 00:39:03,100
That's why all the workload becomes my burden.

384
00:39:04,930 --> 00:39:05,520
Hang in there!

385
00:39:07,700 --> 00:39:08,140
Thank you.

386
00:39:09,390 --> 00:39:09,950
Well then,

387
00:39:10,520 --> 00:39:11,000
I have to go first.

388
00:39:12,080 --> 00:39:12,880
Drive safely.

389
00:39:33,680 --> 00:39:34,290
Jay!

390
00:39:34,820 --> 00:39:36,010
Can you get the water for me?

391
00:39:51,660 --> 00:39:51,950
Here.

392
00:39:53,390 --> 00:39:54,080
Namping!

393
00:40:01,260 --> 00:40:01,850
Does it hurt?

394
00:40:11,320 --> 00:40:11,840
Thank you.

395
00:40:29,150 --> 00:40:29,760
Namping,

396
00:40:32,030 --> 00:40:33,300
what brings you here today?

397
00:40:36,330 --> 00:40:37,150
I want to see the car.

398
00:40:38,430 --> 00:40:39,970
I just want to know what I need to buy.

399
00:40:41,080 --> 00:40:41,860
I want to help.

400
00:40:51,100 --> 00:40:51,440
Oh.

401
00:40:52,430 --> 00:40:54,160
I'll go take a shower first.

402
00:40:54,920 --> 00:40:55,490
Wait.

403
00:40:58,310 --> 00:40:58,920
Sit down.

404
00:41:03,760 --> 00:41:04,730
Let’s treat your wound first.

405
00:41:48,640 --> 00:41:49,450
There's dirt all over.

406
00:41:50,770 --> 00:41:51,220
Oh.

407
00:41:56,230 --> 00:41:56,880
Thank you

408
00:42:02,600 --> 00:42:03,900
for fixing the car for me.

409
00:42:41,940 --> 00:42:42,950
I'll come back again tomorrow.

410
00:42:46,280 --> 00:42:47,020
You should take a rest.

411
00:43:23,750 --> 00:43:24,280
Namping.

412
00:43:25,150 --> 00:43:27,120
I've checked the electrical system,

413
00:43:28,480 --> 00:43:30,240
and I’ll change the battery.

414
00:43:31,230 --> 00:43:34,170
Also, I’ve checked all the systems here already.

415
00:43:34,770 --> 00:43:38,870
They’re still functioning, but I think I will replace them with new ones

416
00:43:39,320 --> 00:43:40,560
so there won’t be any problems in the future.

417
00:44:07,840 --> 00:44:09,870
Namping, can you get me a size 18 wrench?

418
00:44:15,640 --> 00:44:17,760
I want something like this.

419
00:44:19,280 --> 00:44:19,790
Oh!

420
00:44:24,100 --> 00:44:24,660
This one?

421
00:44:25,010 --> 00:44:25,370
Yes.

422
00:44:26,970 --> 00:44:27,870
Can you keep this for me?

423
00:44:39,560 --> 00:44:40,330
It slipped out of my hand.

424
00:45:30,190 --> 00:45:30,730
Thank you.

425
00:45:34,570 --> 00:45:35,170
Are you tired?

426
00:45:36,440 --> 00:45:36,790
Yes.

427
00:45:38,720 --> 00:45:39,380
I'm tired

428
00:45:40,160 --> 00:45:40,980
and hot.

429
00:45:42,420 --> 00:45:43,660
The weather is so hot today.

430
00:45:48,520 --> 00:45:49,240
Are you laughing at me?

431
00:45:49,760 --> 00:45:50,660
No.

432
00:45:52,860 --> 00:45:53,850
- Are you laughing at me?
- No, I'm not.

433
00:45:54,310 --> 00:45:55,020
I'm not laughing at you.

434
00:45:55,810 --> 00:45:56,200
Nope.

435
00:45:56,920 --> 00:45:57,670
Why are you laughing?

436
00:45:58,580 --> 00:45:59,680
Because I'm dirty, huh?

437
00:45:59,730 --> 00:46:00,800
No, you're not dirty at all.

438
00:46:01,210 --> 00:46:02,170
Not at all.

439
00:46:02,800 --> 00:46:03,570
Not dirty at all.

440
00:46:04,400 --> 00:46:05,270
Whoa!

441
00:46:05,530 --> 00:46:06,930
Your hand is so dirty!

442
00:46:08,760 --> 00:46:09,890
You're teasing me, right?

443
00:46:09,920 --> 00:46:10,560
No.

444
00:46:10,700 --> 00:46:11,430
Look at my hand.

445
00:47:33,190 --> 00:47:33,510
How's it going?

446
00:47:35,670 --> 00:47:36,160
Well...

447
00:47:36,880 --> 00:47:37,840
I've changed the electrical system.

448
00:47:37,940 --> 00:47:39,290
I'm not talking about that.

449
00:47:39,570 --> 00:47:40,410
I saw you.

450
00:47:42,700 --> 00:47:43,850
If you're looking at him like that,

451
00:47:45,110 --> 00:47:46,410
just take him to the resort.

452
00:47:47,930 --> 00:47:48,470
Wow.

453
00:47:48,880 --> 00:47:50,370
- But...
- Don't say anything.

454
00:47:51,750 --> 00:47:52,800
Just tell me what you need.

455
00:47:53,540 --> 00:47:54,170
I'll get it for you.

456
00:47:56,600 --> 00:47:57,310
Really?

457
00:47:58,300 --> 00:47:59,190
Have I ever said anything jokingly?

458
00:48:03,760 --> 00:48:04,210
Come on.

459
00:48:05,440 --> 00:48:05,750
Alright?

460
00:48:06,610 --> 00:48:07,390
Just keep fixing it.

461
00:48:07,580 --> 00:48:08,670
I know you're motivated.

462
00:48:09,040 --> 00:48:09,900
Keep going, X.

463
00:48:11,180 --> 00:48:11,970
Thank you!

464
00:48:12,160 --> 00:48:12,670
Okay!

465
00:48:51,700 --> 00:48:55,390
I like to come here alone when I want to think aimlessly.

466
00:49:16,290 --> 00:49:16,880
Namping!

467
00:49:36,120 --> 00:49:36,690
Let's get in the water.

468
00:49:39,220 --> 00:49:39,930
No.

469
00:49:44,020 --> 00:49:44,560
X!

470
00:49:45,840 --> 00:49:47,010
Since we're at the waterfall,

471
00:49:48,420 --> 00:49:49,140
let's go play in the water.

472
00:51:03,080 --> 00:51:04,770
You're making go crazy.

473
00:51:46,170 --> 00:51:47,360
The sky is so beautiful today.

474
00:51:52,230 --> 00:51:53,030
That's because...

475
00:51:55,070 --> 00:51:58,640
Those who say that the sky looks beautiful are in love.

476
00:52:06,370 --> 00:52:08,120
I like when I'm up there.

477
00:52:10,870 --> 00:52:12,690
Sometimes I just want to jump out the window

478
00:52:15,630 --> 00:52:16,890
and float among the clouds.

479
00:52:19,670 --> 00:52:22,260
If you weren't here,

480
00:52:23,510 --> 00:52:25,080
I guess I'd be looking at the sky all day.

481
00:52:31,120 --> 00:52:31,930
Looking at the airplane?

482
00:52:34,960 --> 00:52:36,420
I'm not a dog!

483
00:52:43,380 --> 00:52:44,000
Namping.

484
00:52:45,420 --> 00:52:46,950
You don't want to move back to Thailand?

485
00:53:02,440 --> 00:53:03,050
I do.

486
00:53:05,120 --> 00:53:06,160
So, why not just do it?

487
00:53:16,920 --> 00:53:18,230
Is there someone waiting for you there?

488
00:53:22,570 --> 00:53:23,170
There's no one.

489
00:53:40,300 --> 00:53:41,440
But you have me here.

490
00:53:44,940 --> 00:53:45,990
Can you please not go back?

491
00:54:01,650 --> 00:54:02,900
I'll come back here again next year.

492
00:54:05,590 --> 00:54:06,500
I promise.

493
00:54:11,000 --> 00:54:11,900
How about...

494
00:54:26,210 --> 00:54:27,180
Stop asking.

495
00:54:30,390 --> 00:54:31,570
Can you do it again?

496
00:54:34,660 --> 00:54:35,040
No.

497
00:54:36,560 --> 00:54:37,830
Namping!

498
00:54:40,930 --> 00:54:41,760
Please.

499
00:54:44,720 --> 00:54:45,030
No.

500
00:54:45,890 --> 00:54:47,150
Please.

501
00:54:54,200 --> 00:54:55,320
Stay still.

502
00:54:55,630 --> 00:54:56,150
Just a sec.

503
00:55:04,180 --> 00:55:08,230
♪ How many drops of tears have I shed for love? ♪

504
00:55:08,230 --> 00:55:12,170
♪ Streaming down my face since that day ♪

505
00:55:12,260 --> 00:55:14,340
♪ It took us time to discover our love ♪

506
00:55:14,350 --> 00:55:17,140
♪ To become the dreams we unveil ♪

507
00:55:17,150 --> 00:55:18,980
♪ Never forget about this ♪

508
00:55:18,990 --> 00:55:23,730
♪ Can you promise me that you will never forget me? ♪

509
00:55:35,020 --> 00:55:37,070
I've rescheduled the flight to Switzerland to make it faster.

510
00:55:38,260 --> 00:55:39,130
So that means

511
00:55:39,520 --> 00:55:41,480
Namping has decided not to stay here anymore, right?

512
00:55:42,190 --> 00:55:42,590
Yeah.

513
00:55:42,960 --> 00:55:44,850
I don't know what I did that made him feel sad.

514
00:55:45,800 --> 00:55:46,640
Why did he just leave like that?

515
00:55:48,870 --> 00:55:49,320
Ping.

516
00:55:50,360 --> 00:55:51,710
I think you should reconsider.

517
00:55:52,660 --> 00:55:55,210
I think X will be very happy if you change your mind.

518
00:55:56,880 --> 00:55:59,400
I just want to see you enjoy your life with friends,

519
00:56:00,130 --> 00:56:01,100
family,

520
00:56:02,050 --> 00:56:03,400
and a good partner.
